        <p>For loops execute a code constantly until a condition returns true. Let's start with the simple syntax example, the code below will print every item in an array: </p>
        <div class="code">
            fruits = ["banana", "strawberry", "coconut", "apple"]<br>
            for x in fruits:<br>
                <indent/>print(x)<br>
        </div>
        <p>Code above will output banana, strawberry, coconut, apple. Basically, for is the loop, x is the variable that value is from 0 to 3 the item on the array, fruits is the array, and then we print every item from 0 to 3 </p>
